g.title: noteD19661201
g.text: SUNSPOT was the Block I Command Module AGC
software that would have flown in the Apollo 1
mission and its two immediate follow-ups, had the
Apollo 1 fire not caused all of those missions to
be cancelled. The software, nevertheless, was
complete and ready to fly at the time of the
trajedy. The records are incomplete, however, and
we cannot be sure that 247 was the specific
SUNSPOT revision intended for Apollo 1. However,
it is the highest revision that we are aware of
that was tested for that purpose.
